hireachy structure:
Detailed Explanation (Interview Ready)
1️⃣ Organization (Equivalent to Azure Tenant)

Top-level container

Represents company domain

Central IAM & policies

Linked to Google Workspace / Cloud Identity

👉 Similar to Azure AD Tenant

2️⃣ Folder (Optional Layer)

Used to group projects

For department-based separation

IAM policies can be applied here

Example:

Folder: Production

Folder: Non-Production

Folder: Finance

Folder: DevOps

👉 Azure equivalent: Management Groups

3️⃣ Project (Most Important in GCP)

Everything lives inside a Project

Billing attached at project level

IAM roles assigned at project level

APIs enabled per project

👉 Azure equivalent: Subscription
👉 But also behaves like Resource Group in terms of scoping.

💡 Key Interview Line:

In GCP, Project is the primary isolation boundary for billing, IAM, and resources.

4️⃣ VPC Network

Created inside a Project

Global resource in GCP (important difference!)

Can have subnets across multiple regions

👉 Azure VNet is regional
👉 GCP VPC is global

5️⃣ Subnet

Regional resource

Created inside VPC

Defines IP range
________________________

6️⃣ Resources

Inside Project:

Compute Engine (VM)

GKE

Cloud SQL

Load Balancer

Cloud Storage

IAM policies

Firewall rules
